The claim with the title 'PoliGraph: Johnson’s polling claim misleads ' says Mark Twain once said that “ there are three kinds of lies: lies, damned lies and statistics. ”That quote applies to a recent statement made by Republican gubernatorial candidate Jeff Johnson, who says two polls show he is within striking distance of gov. Mark Dayton. “ Mark Dayton is in trouble, ” reads the headline of a recent Johnson press release. “ these polls confirm that Mark Dayton is in trouble, and that i am in a great position with the general election campaign just underway. ”A separate post on Johnson’s Facebook page said “ Mark Dayton is under 50%! We are only single digits away from victory! ”Dayton is in better shape than Johnson lets on. 
